        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Most machine translation systems construct translations from a closed vocabulary of target word forms , ",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "posing problems ",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "for translating into languages ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "that have productive compounding processes . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We present a simple and effective approach ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "that deals with this problem in two phases . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "First , we build a classifier ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that identifies spans of the input text ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "that can be translated into a single compound word in the target language . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "Then , for each identified span , we generate a pool of possible compounds ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "which are added to the translation model as `` synthetic '' phrase translations . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Experiments reveal ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "that ( i ) we can effectively predict ",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "what spans can be compounded ; ",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "( ii ) our compound generation model produces good compounds ; ",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "and ( iii ) modest improvements are possible in end-to-end English-German and English-Finnish translation tasks . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "We additionally introduce KomposEval , a new multi-reference dataset of English phrases and their translations into German compounds . <S>",
